    <header class="faq-page-header">
        <h1>FAQs</h1>
        <p class="faq-updated">Updated August 2025</p>
    </header>

    <div class="faq-accordion-list">
        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>What should I do if I encounter a bug?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>We’ve built Volo to be as reliable as possible, but if you do find a bug, please let us know. You can report any issues directly on our <a href="https://github.com/thisisrogerflanagan/volo-releases/issues/new?template=bug_report.yml" target="_blank">GitHub repository</a> or email us at support@voloapp.com.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>Why is the like button disabled?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>The like button is currently a visual element to maintain the aesthetic of the board. We’re working on integrating it with music services in a future update to allow you to save your favorite tracks directly.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>Why is the waveform simulated?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>Volo uses a beautifully crafted simulation to represent the "pulse" of your audio without requiring complex permissions. This ensures a private, performant experience that still feels alive and connected to your music.</p>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>
                <h3>How do I hide the menu bar icon?</h3>
                <span class="faq-toggle-icon"></span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <p>You can toggle the visibility of the menu bar icon in the Volo Settings menu. Simply right-click the icon (if visible) or use the shortcut Command + Comma within the app to access preferences.</p>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>

    <footer class="faq-help-footer">
        <h2>Have more questions?</h2>
        <p>If you have any additional questions, do not hesitate to <a href="mailto:support@voloapp.com" class="faq-contact-link">contact us</a>.</p>
    </footer>
</div>

<script>
    const details = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-accordion-list details');
    details.forEach((targetDetail) => {
        targetDetail.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
            // Only trigger if we're opening, not closing
            if (!targetDetail.hasAttribute('open')) {
                details.forEach((detail) => {
                    if (detail !== targetDetail) {
                        detail.removeAttribute('open');
                    }
                });
            }
        });
    });
</script>
